Domestic flights have been given the all-clear and are being allowed to fly between OR Tambo, King Shaka, Cape Town and Lanseria International Airports. JOHANNESBURG - Business travellers can once again take to the skies under Level 3 of the lockdown. Domestic flights have been given the all-clear and are being allowed to fly between OR Tambo, King Shaka, Cape Town and Lanseria International Airports. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula said strict restrictions will guide the number of flights per day based on the reason for travel. READ: Limited domestic flights available under level 3 The minister said the resumption of domestic flights will be rolled out in three phases. Planes are allowed to be filled to 100 percent capacity because they're using High-Efficiency Particulate Air filters. OR Tambo International Airport General Manager Bongiwe Pityi-Vokwana said it's important for passengers to know that "we are now in a new normal". READ: Lanseria ready for take-off "They need to set aside two hours before they get on their flight," she said. "This is to ensure that they are able to access the airport without any challenges." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.